1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,500
You Can Be Anything turns a personal profile,
an opening line, and five choices into a complete story.

2
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:25,000
I enter a protagonist, MBTI, visual style, mood,
genre, and an original opening sentence.

3
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:36,500
GPT-5.6 Luna is the default story engine.
The first request creates three contextual choices.

4
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:48,000
After I choose, Luna writes two story paragraphs
that continue my opening instead of starting over.

5
00:00:48,000 --> 00:01:06,000
The selected scene and its established facts become
context for Growth and the next three choices.

6
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:23,500
Every decision triggers one advance request,
so the Crisis responds to the path I actually selected.

7
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:43,500
The same continuity carries through Climax.
Unselected branches do not consume long-form output.

8
00:01:43,500 --> 00:02:07,000
Resolution completes a six-request live cycle:
one initial choice request and five story advances.

9
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:17,500
The finale preserves my path under Origin, Growth,
Crisis, Climax, Resolution, and Epilogue.

10
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:27,000
Each playthrough has one session ID and one archive,
containing readable story text and structured history.

11
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Finale illustration is optional.
The game shows the maximum cost before any request.

12
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:46,000
I used GPT-5.6 through Codex to implement the Luna proxy,
validation, cost-aware caching, and session archives.

13
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:53,000
The completed image is attached to the same session
as its story, while duplicate requests remain blocked.

14
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,000
Every path becomes a story worth keeping.
